    selectCount: 3,
    rationale: "Rome IV criteria for functional constipation include: <3 BM/week, straining in \u226525% of defecations, lumpy/hard stools in \u226525%, sensation of incomplete evacuation in \u226525%, sensation of anorectal obstruction in \u226525%, and manual maneuvers to facilitate defecation in \u226525%. Choices A, B, and D directly match these criteria. Nocturnal defecation urgency (C) is a red flag for organic pathology and is not a feature of functional constipation. Loose stools rarely present without laxatives (E) is actually a criterion for IBS-C or functional constipation but is listed as an exclusion criterion \u2014 loose stools should be rare without laxatives to support the diagnosis, making this a nuanced point; however, it is not one of the primary positive criteria tested here.",
