    rationale: "Secondary constipation has an identifiable underlying cause that, when treated, resolves the constipation. Opioids (via mu-receptor inhibition of peristalsis), hypothyroidism (via reduced metabolic rate slowing colonic transit), and anticholinergics (via muscarinic blockade of intestinal smooth muscle) are classic secondary causes requiring targeted treatment. IBS-C is itself a functional disorder \u2014 it is not a secondary cause of constipation but rather a separate functional diagnosis. Low dietary fiber intake is a contributing lifestyle factor but is not classified as a secondary cause in the same category as systemic disease or medications.",
