    rationale: "An expansile pulsatile epigastric mass in a high-risk patient (elderly male smoker with hypertension) raises strong concern for AAA. The appropriate next step is abdominal ultrasound, which is the first-line imaging modality for AAA detection and measurement. It is non-invasive, inexpensive, and highly accurate for aortic diameter. Emergency surgery is not indicated for an asymptomatic AAA \u2014 surgical intervention is typically considered when diameter exceeds 5.5 cm or when the aneurysm is symptomatic or rapidly expanding. Proceeding with elective surgery without evaluation would be unsafe. An ECG does not assess aortic pathology.",
