    rationale: "USPSTF recommends routine screening for all adults aged 45\u201375. For ages 76\u201385, the recommendation shifts to an individualized decision, weighing the patient's overall health, life expectancy, prior screening history, and personal preferences. Screening is not automatically discontinued at 76, nor is it universally mandated. Any approved modality (FIT, colonoscopy, sigmoidoscopy) remains valid based on clinical context.",
