    rationale: "FIT detects occult (hidden) blood in stool, which may indicate early colorectal cancer or advanced adenomas. A positive FIT triggers diagnostic colonoscopy, which can then identify and remove precancerous lesions. FIT itself does not remove polyps \u2014 that is the mechanism of colonoscopy. CEA is a tumor marker used for monitoring, not screening. Stool DNA tests (like Cologuard) detect DNA mutations, but FIT specifically detects hemoglobin.",
