    rationale: "Epigastric hernias protrude through defects in the linea alba between the xiphoid process and the umbilicus (above the umbilicus). Umbilical hernias protrude specifically through the umbilical ring \u2014 the fibromuscular opening through which the umbilical vessels passed in fetal life. Both involve the linea alba broadly, but the specific anatomical location distinguishes them. Umbilical hernias are common in infants and multiparous women; epigastric hernias are not exclusively congenital.",
