    rationale: "Incisional hernias occur at prior surgical sites where the fascial layers were divided and subsequently failed to heal with adequate tensile strength. Factors such as infection, obesity, poor nutrition, and wound dehiscence increase risk. The bulge at the exact site of a prior incision that increases with Valsalva (increased intra-abdominal pressure) is the classic presentation. Spigelian hernias occur at the lateral edge of the rectus sheath, not at incision sites. Epigastric and umbilical hernias occur at midline locations.",
