    rationale: "Mallampati Class III is defined by visualization of only the soft palate base, with the uvula and tonsillar pillars obscured by the tongue. This indicates a relatively large tongue relative to oropharyngeal space, predicting limited or absent glottic visualization during direct laryngoscopy. Class I shows the full soft palate, uvula, and tonsillar pillars. Class II shows the soft palate and uvula but not the pillars. Class IV shows only the hard palate. Class III and IV predict difficult laryngoscopy, but Class III does not mandate a surgical airway \u2014 it warrants preparation and alternative strategies.",
